knows what that is. So...

00:14.208 --> 00:17.417
-I don't, Sir.
-[Gerry sighs]

00:17.458 --> 00:21.083
Could somebody please tell
Lori what moral rela...ins...?

00:24.166 --> 00:26.417
Fine, Sheila, go ahead.

00:26.458 --> 00:30.083
-Descriptive moral relativism
holds that some people disagree
about what is moral.

00:30.125 --> 00:32.333
-Okay.

00:32.375 --> 00:36.959
-Meta-ethical moral relativism
holds that nobody is objectively
right or wrong...

00:37.000 --> 00:39.208
-Nobody.

00:39.250 --> 00:41.208
Got it? Easy.

00:41.250 --> 00:44.041
Now if we could stick to the
questions that I assigned,
please.

00:44.083 --> 00:46.500
-And, what is
cultural relativism?

00:46.542 --> 00:48.959
-[Half whispers]: Who cares?

00:49.000 --> 00:51.166
[Gerry]: Sheila?

00:51.208 --> 00:53.375
-Cultural relativism is a
principle that was established

00:53.417 --> 00:56.333
as axiomatic in anthropological
research by Franz Boas.

00:56.375 --> 00:58.291
-[Quietly]: That it?

01:01.208 --> 01:03.333
-You can't stump me Lori.
