-Felt good though.

15:35.041 --> 15:37.041
[♪ Music]

15:37.083 --> 15:39.291
-You wanted to see...

15:41.041 --> 15:43.083
Hey David. How's it going buddy?

15:43.125 --> 15:46.375
Mr. Duncan, David tells
me you got him alone and

15:46.417 --> 15:50.166
you threatened [bleep]
and then [bleep] [bleep] again.

15:50.208 --> 15:53.166
And then you growled.
-Excuse me? What? I...?

15:53.208 --> 15:55.000
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

15:56.333 --> 15:58.500
-He said that sir,
I swear he did.

15:58.542 --> 16:00.875
-What?

16:00.917 --> 16:03.250
What are you doing? What is...?

16:03.291 --> 16:08.083
Why would I say any of that to
a student to risk losing my job?

16:08.125 --> 16:11.291
This is...What's going on here?
-Do you have a witness?

16:11.333 --> 16:14.125
-[Quietly]: No, he doesn't.
-No sir, but he planned that.

16:14.166 --> 16:16.375
I swear, he did this.

16:17.166 --> 16:19.875
Sir this is ludicrous.
Can I go?

16:19.917 --> 16:22.583
'Cause I have marking to do.
I want to plan next
months lessons. Like...

16:22.625 --> 16:27.291
-Hang on. David, I'm going to
have to side with Mr. Duncan
on this.

16:27.333 --> 16:29.792
It just seems pretty
far fetched to me.
-Thank you.

16:29.834 --> 16:33.208
-What? Are you kidding me?
-[Quietly]: No, he's not.

16:33.250 --> 16:36.333
-David, stop wasting everybody's
time. Smarten up.

16:36.375 --> 16:40.208
-Sir, he's crazy. You
have to believe me.
-Blah.

16:40.250 --> 16:42.250
-I think my parents
should know about him.

16:42.291 --> 16:44.542
-Alright, we could do that.

16:44.583 --> 16:47.250
Let's have your parents come in,
I'll tell them about the five

16:47.291 --> 16:49.959
other teachers who have
complained about your
insubordination.

16:50.000 --> 16:51.750
Should we do that?

16:52.625 --> 16:55.041
-[Gerry takes a deep breath]
-No sir.

16:55.083 --> 16:57.208
-I thought not.
Goodbye David.

16:58.208 --> 17:00.333
-Bye David.

17:04.417 --> 17:11.000
-Well, I tell ya, it's like they
got nothing to do but come
in and cause problems.

17:11.041 --> 17:14.917
Waste your time. Who were
the other five teachers?

17:14.959 --> 17:17.166
-No other teachers.

17:17.208 --> 17:20.000
-Duncan, I know about
the no witness trick.

17:20.041 --> 17:22.417
-What are you talking about?
-You get to use that once.

17:24.083 --> 17:27.166
-[Gerry takes a deep breath]:
One time...One more time?

17:27.208 --> 17:29.667
-Never again.
-Oh come on.

17:29.709 --> 17:33.375
It worked. Look, he respects
me now. He's afraid.

17:33.417 --> 17:35.417
-Never again.

17:38.125 --> 17:40.625
[♪ Music]

17:40.667 --> 17:43.000
[♪ Music]

17:49.250 --> 17:52.375
-I'm busy Malik.
-But I've arrived.

17:52.417 --> 17:54.709
-And?
-Don't tell me.

17:54.750 --> 17:57.000
-I saw the sequel.
-Ugh.

17:57.041 --> 18:00.166
-How do you have any fans?
That thing was a piece of...

18:00.208 --> 18:03.458
-It never aired back home.
I make sure of that.

18:03.500 --> 18:06.250
-Mmm hmm. Well here's
the thing George Clooney.

18:06.291 --> 18:09.125
Some kid puked his body weight
up on the third floor, so...

18:09.166 --> 18:12.208
Why don't you shimmy on
up there and clean it up?

18:12.250 --> 18:14.208
Thank you.

18:15.834 --> 18:17.875
Nope.

18:19.375 --> 18:21.500
Such a shame.

18:23.375 --> 18:26.333
-Got chicken fingers and
root beer for supper tonight.
-[Simon inhales excitedly]

18:26.375 --> 18:28.709
-So that's it? You
guys just made up?

18:28.750 --> 18:31.792
-Yeah, I can't remember why
we were fighting to begin
with to be honest.

18:31.834 --> 18:34.125
Anyway, thanks for letting
me hang. It was fun.

18:34.166 --> 18:36.250
-It was, you wanna come
again on Saturday?

18:36.291 --> 18:39.083
-Oh no, mom and I go
to the zoo on Saturday's.

18:39.125 --> 18:41.667
-Maybe you would like to
come to the zoo too Bill?

18:41.709 --> 18:44.709
-Yeah, Saturday's are
busy for me. But...

18:44.750 --> 18:46.959
Sunday? Watch football?

18:47.000 --> 18:49.166
-Prayer day?

18:49.208 --> 18:51.458
-Well, if you ever run away
from home again I'm here. So...

18:51.500 --> 18:53.959
-Thanks. That's good to know.

18:55.375 --> 18:58.333
-Maybe we'll, ah, both run away.

18:58.375 --> 19:01.291
-Yeah, or maybe just Simon.

19:02.250 --> 19:04.667
-Or maybe just my mom.
Look at this.

19:04.709 --> 19:08.458
[Simon laughs]: Gonna have to
put you in the zoo ya old
jungle cat.

19:08.500 --> 19:10.458
-[Angela mouths]: Bye Bill.
-See ya.

19:10.500 --> 19:14.291
[♪ Music]
♪ Now I, I wanna know ♪

19:14.333 --> 19:17.333
♪ What it took to leave me ♪

19:17.375 --> 19:21.834
♪ Now I, I wanna know ♪

19:21.875 --> 19:25.417
♪ How would you fall
How would you ♪

19:25.458 --> 19:29.417
♪ Goodbye and it starts
to snow ♪

19:29.458 --> 19:31.750
♪ In the streets... ♪
[Door slams, music stops]

19:33.500 --> 19:35.792
-Hey sir, are you ever going
to hand back our assignments?

19:35.834 --> 19:38.500
-Okay, I'll have those tests
for you next week. Okay?

19:38.542 --> 19:41.000
-You said that two weeks ago.
What a joke.

19:42.083 --> 19:45.333
-Excuse me?
-Drop it. Trust me just drop it.

19:45.375 --> 19:47.583
-Thank you David.
-What?

19:47.625 --> 19:50.000
-Say you're sorry, 'cause if you
don't he promises he'll make

19:50.041 --> 19:54.959
every single day here a living
hell for you. And then [bleep]
he'll take you out the [bleep].

19:55.000 --> 20:00.125
-Can...Can he do that?
-I don't even know anymore, man.

20:00.166 --> 20:03.208
-Sorry sir.
-Apology accepted.

20:04.083 --> 20:06.792
[♪ Music]

20:07.667 --> 20:09.959
[♪ Music]

20:10.000 --> 20:12.417
-What was it like to
teach in the 60's dad?

20:12.458 --> 20:15.208
-Let me tell you,
it wasn't easy.

20:15.250 --> 20:18.500
Drugs. Rock and roll. Vietnam.

20:18.542 --> 20:22.542
It was rough. Not like
today Gerry.

20:22.583 --> 20:24.709
-How bad were the
kids back then?

20:24.750 --> 20:28.458
-[Francis chortles]: Just like
yours, only 10 times worse.

20:28.500 --> 20:30.667
-[Class]: Good morning
Mr. Duncan.

20:30.709 --> 20:32.709
-Open your books.

20:33.667 --> 20:36.417
-Sir, I have a question
about the homework.

20:38.834 --> 20:41.041
-[David grimaces]: Ah.

20:41.083 --> 20:45.500
-What did I tell you about
raising your hand before
speaking?

20:45.542 --> 20:49.000
-[Class]: If you want to speak,
you must raise your hand.

20:49.041 --> 20:51.375
-That's right.

20:51.417 --> 20:53.834
-[Lighter clicks]

20:54.750 --> 20:58.417
-Anyone got a light?
-[Lighter clicks]

20:58.458 --> 21:03.500
-[Gerry]: I cannot imagine
Jimmy and David ten times worse.

21:03.542 --> 21:05.500
-Oh yes.

21:05.542 --> 21:08.875
-I feel so sorry for
teachers back then.
-It was terrible.

21:08.917 --> 21:13.166
That's right!
[Ruler hits desk hard]

21:14.333 --> 21:16.458
-Good for you dad.
-Thanks son.

21:16.500 --> 21:19.542
-Man, I never knew
how hard you had it.
-Oh yeah.
